messages.message: @shaunak here is a snapshot of a crash when celery had 12gb of ram. It crashed around 9.1gb mark. Unclear why it didn't capitalize on the remainder of the memory
The document has 4476 pages and it fails while processing 4475-4476 pages.
Do you think it fails *after* the pdf-processing is complete, but *before* process file ends.  We actually construct the IBOCR during that step (along with writing images to disk etc.)
